   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Ninety-five THE RIGHTEOUS ONE SUBSTITUTED</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR THE UNRIGHTEOUS ONES Scripture: 1 Pet 3:18 Jesus is the righteous One Jesus is God coming as man.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Jesus was born in holiness without the nature of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jesus has never committed sin.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Once He asked publicly, Who among you can prove that I have sinned?</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>When He was examined before His crucifixion, no one could find sin in Him.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Jesus is the sinless and the righteous One.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>We are the unrighteous ones We are sinners.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>We were born in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>We have committed sins and grew up in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>We are altogether, one hundred percent sinners.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The righteous One substituted for the unrighteous ones The righteous One substituted Himself for the unrighteous ones; that is, the Lord Jesus substituted Himself for us.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>On the cross the Lord Jesus became our substitute by bearing our sins, shedding His blood, and dying for us.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Because He bore our sins and died for us on the cross, our sins are forgiven before God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Because He died for us, we can be delivered from death and can obtain eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>How to partake of Jesus substitution</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
